<plot>A cellist freely interprets a few famous themes from Puccini's La Boheme. A camera films the musical "performance" from very close up. Shot in a single take, the point is not to tell a story, but to attempt to render the pure moment in which music emerges and an image is formed.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?634574</url></doc>
